CatDescriptText: Cutline of related images and article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, national edition, October 16, 1943, pgs. 1, 4, 5, 11 & 20, reads: "Ship To Symbolize Ideals Of Robert L. Vann - With fitting ceremonies, the 'S.S. Robert L. Vann,' ...was christened Sunday in New England shipbuilding yards in South Portland, Maine, after being blessed by the Rev. C.E. Askew of Detroit..."
TitMainTitle: Jessie Vann christening Liberty Ship SS Robert L. Vann, with Mable Page Johnson holding bouquet of flowers, Portland, Maine
